Pad geohashes with neighboring one-level smaller geohashes

Source: R/utils.R
gh_pad.Rd

Pad geohashes with neighboring one-level smaller geohash

gh_pad(ghs, self = TRUE)

Arguments

ghs

(character vector) geohashes
self

(flag) Whether the input geohash should be included in the output

Value

(list of character vectors) of padding geohashes

Examples

gh_pad(c("tdr1w", "tdr1q"))
#> $tdr1w
#>  [1] "tdr1w"  "tdr1mz" "tdr1qp" "tdr1qr" "tdr1qx" "tdr1qz" "tdr1rp" "tdr1tb"
#>  [9] "tdr1tc" "tdr1tf" "tdr1tg" "tdr1tu" "tdr1tv" "tdr1ty" "tdr1tz" "tdr1x0"
#> [17] "tdr1x1" "tdr1x4" "tdr1x5" "tdr1xh" "tdr1xj" "tdr1xn" "tdr1xp" "tdr1vb"
#> [25] "tdr1y0" "tdr1y2" "tdr1y8" "tdr1yb" "tdr1z0"
#> 
#> $tdr1q
#>  [1] "tdr1q"  "tdr1jz" "tdr1np" "tdr1nr" "tdr1nx" "tdr1nz" "tdr1pp" "tdr1mb"
#>  [9] "tdr1mc" "tdr1mf" "tdr1mg" "tdr1mu" "tdr1mv" "tdr1my" "tdr1mz" "tdr1r0"
#> [17] "tdr1r1" "tdr1r4" "tdr1r5" "tdr1rh" "tdr1rj" "tdr1rn" "tdr1rp" "tdr1tb"
#> [25] "tdr1w0" "tdr1w2" "tdr1w8" "tdr1wb" "tdr1x0"
#> 
mapview::mapview(geohashTools::gh_to_sf(gh_pad("tdr1w")[[1]]))
